author: philipdefranco
description: Trump‚Äôs Tariffs Are Working And He‚Äôs Really Mad At Walmart #usa #america  Trump is now blaming Walmart for rising prices in response to the tariffs. He says that they should eat the cost of the tariffs and not raise prices on customers. This tweet from Trump reveals what many suspected, Trump doesn‚Äôt understand how his tariffs are supposed to work. If prices don‚Äôt rise in response to tariffs then they don‚Äôt deliver any protection. The tariffs only work because the prices go up. The tariffs are supposed to make Chinese goods more expensive than American goods. That‚Äôs the whole point. If Walmart eats the prices on the tariffs, then there‚Äôs no incentive for consumers to choose the American-made version of products, if it even exists, because they are at a base line more expensive. Trump‚Äôs policy is working exactly how it‚Äôs intended to and he doesn‚Äôt like it. Trump also claimed that countries pay the tariffs, not consumers - which obviously judging by Walmart raising their prices is not true. Oh a more zoomed out level - Trump also said that the tariffs are there to replace the income tax and make us rich but that they are also there to increase manufacturing, it can‚Äôt be both. If you import less goods because you‚Äôre producing more domestically, the less tax revenue you‚Äôre getting and the less ‚Äúrich‚Äù you‚Äôre becoming. This is like basic Econ 101 stuff.

author: motherprimal
description: Before the rib, there was the clay. And from that same clay, Adam and Lilith were formed ‚Äî equal. Elemental. Earth-born. But when Lilith would not lay beneath him, when she claimed her voice, her pleasure, her power ‚Äî she was cast out, not for sin‚Ä¶ but for sovereignty. This is not just mythology. This is memory. Lilith is not a demon. She is the first woman to say no. The first to walk away when the divine masculine forgot how to revere the divine feminine. The first to name herself. Banished from Eden, she did not crumble. She transformed. She became the night wind. The whisper in the trees. The fire in the womb. They feared her because she could not be controlled. They called her wicked because she remembered her worth. They wrote her out ‚Äî but she never truly left. Lilith is the energy that rises when we choose ourselves. When we refuse to shrink. When we wake from the spell of silence and say: ‚ÄúI remember who I am.‚Äù To all who have been told they are too much, too wild, too angry, too sensual, too loud: Lilith walks with you. This is not the end of her story. It is the beginning of her reclamation If she‚Äôs been showing up in your dreams, your rituals, or your rage ‚Äî this may be your Lilith initiation. Drop a black heart if you feel her rising. #lilith #goddess #mythology #fyp #darkfeminine
